      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PERSIAN WONDER (1) is back after a three-month spell. Form last prep included a 1.2-length defeat by Warwoven in the Pago Pago and a second in the Group 3 Baillieu. Trialled twice in readiness for this. Has the class edge which should be enough. The threat probably comes from Gai and Adrian's first starter ARGANSORT (2) who won a recent Randwick trial in good style. Should go fast and might be tough to catch around this tight circuit. LIGHTHORSEMAN (6) started favourite but never looked a chance on debut at Gosford a fortnight ago. Should have more to offer than that. STATEROOM (7) is a full brother to the Group 2 winner Astern on debut for the Maher stable. It will pay to keep an eye on the betting. ADAPTATION (4) showed glimpses of ability last prep and can run well while fresh.",
